  • Package model

    • Class model.MinesweeperBoard extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      1L

      • Serialized Fields

        • valBoard

          int[][] valBoard
          2D array representing the current status of the board populated by values in range [-1,8] inclusive representing how many mines a location is touching or -1 if the location is a mine.

        • visibleBoard

          int[][] visibleBoard
          2D array representing the current status of the board populated by 0 for invisible, 1 for visible, and -2 for flag.

        • visibles

          java.util.HashSet<E> visibles
          HashSet containing OrderedPair objects for all coordinates on the grid visible to the player.

        • dnes

          java.util.HashSet<E> dnes
          A set of all the "Does Not Exist" Ordered Pair locations on the board.

        • rows

          int rows
          The number of rows in the current board.

        • cols

          int cols
          The number of columns in the current board.

        • mineLocs

          java.util.HashSet<E> mineLocs
          HashSet containing OrderedPair objects for all coordinates on the grid containing mines.

        • adjacencies

          java.util.HashMap<K,V> adjacencies
          HashMap that contains an adjacency list for each coordinate in the grid. Each key has a list of all neighboring positions on the grid.

        • initialized

          boolean initialized
          Flag to determine if mines and proximity locations have been placed on the valBoard.

        • score

          int score
          The current runtime of the current game. This is stored here to be serialized.

        • difficulty

          java.lang.String difficulty
          Difficulty mode the current board. This is stored here to be serialized.

        • shape

          java.lang.String shape
          Current shape of the board. It will either be rectangle, diamond, hexagon, triangle or custom.

        • flags

          int flags
          Tracks the number of flags available for use.
